pattern_sources.author: Sue Smith
pattern_sources.name: Ear savers for face masks
pattern_sources.notes:
Wear these colorful ear protectors and feel comfortable with your face mask. Health care providers are getting struggling with wounds behind their ears from the constant mask usage. The main features of this protector are to eliminate uncomfortable tight strings around ears and loose masks that won’t fit. It can be made in any size you want, You can make large amount and donate also.

These patterns are quick, easy and designed especially for beginners, and only use a small amount of yarn so they’re great for using up leftovers from other projects.

I hope you stay safe & healthy. Happy crocheting!
